#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:562
#, no-c-format
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "Glosar"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:565
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>A</title>"
msgstr "<title>A</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "active task"
msgstr "aktivno opravilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid "A task which has a timer running."
msgstr "Opravilo, pri katerem teče časovnik."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>D</title>"
msgstr "<title>D</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:575
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>&DBus;</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>&DBus;</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "An interprocess communication protocol. Short for Desktop Bus."
msgstr "Medprocesni komunikacijski protokol. Okrajšava za Desktop Bus."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "desktop"
msgstr "namizje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&GNU;/&Linux;, FreeBSD and other systems that run X.Org Server have multiple "
"desktops. You can typically have four different desktops installed by "
"default. Each desktop can display its own set of programs and files. When "
"&kde; &plasma; first starts up, the desktop you see is Desktop 1. If you "
"press <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>, you "
"will see Desktop 2. Pressing <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F1</"
"keycap></keycombo> will bring back Desktop 1."
msgstr ""
"&GNU;/&Linux;, FreeBSD in drugi sistemi, ki poganjajo X.Org Server, imajo "
"več namizij. Običajno imate lahko privzeto nameščena štiri različna namizja. "
"Vsako namizje lahko prikaže svoj niz programov in datotek. Ko &kde; &plasma; "
"ko se prvič zažene, je namizje, ki ga vidite, Namizje 1. Če pritisnete "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>, boste "
"videli Namizje 2. S pritiskom <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>F1</"
"keycap></keycombo> bo vrnil Namizje 1."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:592
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>H</title>"
msgstr "<title>H</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "history"
msgstr "zgodovina"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &ktimetracker; is configured to log history, it will record every start/"
"stop timer event. This history is not cleared when times are reset and "
"remains on file until the task is deleted."
msgstr ""
"Če &ktimetracker; je konfiguriran za beleženje zgodovine, bo zabeležil vsak "
"dogodek časovnika za zagon/ustavitev. Ta zgodovina se ne izbriše, ko se časi "
"ponastavijo, in ostane v datoteki, dokler opravilo ni izbrisano."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>S</title>"
msgstr "<title>S</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid "session"
msgstr "seja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:604
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A user-defined starting point for the session timers. A new session begins "
"when you select <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Start New "
"Session</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>. Session data is not saved when you "
"create a new session."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniško določena začetna točka za časovnike seje. Nova seja se začne, ko "
"izberete <menuchoice> <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Začni novo "
"sejo</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>. Podatki o seji se ne shranijo, ko "
"ustvarite novo sejo."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "system tray"
msgstr "sistemski pladenj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:615
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system tray is in the bar that (by default in &kde; &plasma;) appears at "
"the bottom of the screen. In this system tray <inlinemediaobject> "
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"systray.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></"
"imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> the &ktimetracker; icon is on the far "
"right."
msgstr ""
"Sistemski pladenj je v vrstici, ki se (privzeto v &kde; &plasma;) prikaže na "
"dnu zaslona. V tem sistemskem pladnju <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> "
"<imagedata fileref=\"systray.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> &ktimetracker; ikona je skrajno desno."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:624
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>T</title>"
msgstr "<title>T</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:626
#, no-c-format
msgid "top level task"
msgstr "opravilo na najvišji ravni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:627
#, no-c-format
msgid "A task with no parent tasks."
msgstr "Opravilo brez nadrejenih opravil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "&DBus; Interface"
msgstr "&DBus; Vmesnik"

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>version</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>različica</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:651
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>version</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>različica</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:652
#, no-c-format
msgid "Return &ktimetracker;'s version."
msgstr "Vrni različico &ktimetracker;."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:655
#, no-c-format
msgid "QString version()"
msgstr "Različica QString()"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:658 index.docbook:677 index.docbook:743
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Opis"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>version()</function> is a &DBus; call that returns "
"&ktimetracker;'s version number; for example 4.3.1. The version number is "
"returned as a string in the typical &GNU; format of major.minor.bugfix."
msgstr ""
"<function>version()</function> je &DBus; klic, ki vrne številko različice "
"&ktimetracker; na primer 4.3.1. Številka različice je vrnjena kot niz v "
"tipičnem &GNU; oblika major.minor.bugfix."

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:667
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>quit</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>zapusti</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:670
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>quit</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>zapusti</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:671
#, no-c-format
msgid "Quit &ktimetracker;'."
msgstr "Končaj &ktimetracker;'."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid "QString quit()"
msgstr "QString quit()"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:678
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>quit()</function> is a &DBus; call that provides a way that an "
"external program can gracefully shutdown &ktimetracker;."
msgstr ""
"<function>quit()</function> je &DBus; klic, ki omogoča, da lahko zunanji "
"program elegantno zaustavi &ktimetracker;."

#. Tag: refentrytitle
#: index.docbook:721
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refentrytitle>addTask</refentrytitle>"
msgstr "<refentrytitle>addTask</refentrytitle>"

#. Tag: refname
#: index.docbook:724
#, no-c-format
msgid "<refname>addTask</refname>"
msgstr "<refname>addTask</refname>"

#. Tag: refpurpose
#: index.docbook:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add new task."
msgstr "Dodajte novo nalogo."

#. Tag: synopsis
#: index.docbook:728
#, no-c-format
msgid "QString addTask(QString taskname)"
msgstr "QString addTask(QString ime opravila)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "Parametri"

#. Tag: parameter
#: index.docbook:733
#, no-c-format
msgid "taskname"
msgstr "ime opravila"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:735
#, no-c-format
msgid "The name of new task."
msgstr "Ime novega opravila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:744
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<function>addTask(QString taskname)</function> is a &DBus; call that adds a "
"new top-level to-do to the current storage. The UID of the new task is "
"returned."
msgstr ""
"<function>addTask(QString taskname)</function> je &DBus; klic, ki trenutnemu "
"pomnilniku doda novo opravilo na najvišji ravni. Vrne se UID novega opravila."
